dc_description_s: These data layers represent public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2018. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, NSauk_PLSS_2018.gdbN. The feature layers included in this geodatabase are NSauk_PLSSCorners_2018N, NSauk_PLSSQuarterSection_2018N, NSauk_PLSSSection_2018N, and NSauk_PLSSTownship_2018N. [PLSSCorners: The current control point on the surface of the earth and its associated current coordinate value, generally determined by a surveying process and used to define an extremity of a boundary.PLSSQuarterSection: The second division of the PLSS and commonly called a quarter section.PLSSSection: The first division of the PLSS and commonly called a section.PLSSTownship: In the Public Land Survey System a Township refers to a unit of land, that is nominally six miles on a side, usually containing 36 sections.]
dct_provenance_s: Arthur H. Robinson Map Library - University of Wisconsin
